      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Admin Panel</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Permission Matrix</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">
        The Permission Matrix gives you fine-grained control over what each role can do.
        It is split into two sections: <strong>Endpoint Permissions</strong>, which govern
        access to API actions site-wide, and <strong>Subforum Permissions</strong>, which
        govern what each role can do inside each individual subforum.
      </p>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Roles</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Both matrices use the same three roles:
      </p>
      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">guest</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Unregistered visitors.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">user</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Logged-in registered members.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">admin</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Administrators with full site access.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="docs-p">
        Check a box to grant the permission to that role; uncheck to revoke it.
        Changes take effect immediately after saving.
      </p>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Endpoint Permissions</h2>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-permission-matrix-endpoints.png" alt="Endpoint Permission Matrix screenshot" />
      </div>

      <p class="docs-p">
        Endpoint permissions control access to individual API actions across the entire site,
        regardless of which subforum a member is in. Each row is one action — browsing pages,
        creating characters, managing factions, handling currency transactions, posting, and more.
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Use this matrix to answer questions like: <em>can guests browse character lists?</em>
        or <em>can regular users update currency amounts?</em>
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        Admin is typically checked for every endpoint. Be cautious when granting
        sensitive actions (currency management, global settings) to guest or user roles.
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Subforum Permissions</h2>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-permission-matrix-subforums.png" alt="Subforum Permission Matrix screenshot" />
      </div>

      <p class="docs-p">
        Subforum permissions are scoped per subforum — each subforum gets its own block of rows.
        This lets you have different rules for different boards: guests might be able to view
        one subforum but not another, or users might be able to post in general topics but
        not create character topics in a restricted area.
      </p>

      <p class="docs-p">The per-subforum actions available are:</p>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">View subforum</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can see this subforum and its topic list at all.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Post in subforum</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can reply to existing topics.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Create general topic</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can start a new out-of-character thread.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Create character topic</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can create a new character sheet thread.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Create wanted character topic</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can post a wanted character listing.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Create episode topic</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can start a new in-character game thread.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Edit own post / Edit others' post</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can edit their own posts, or posts written by other members.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Edit own topic / Edit others' topic</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can edit the topic header of their own threads, or others'.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta"><div class="field-name">Delete own topic / Delete others' topic</div></div>
          <div class="field-desc">Whether the role can delete threads they started, or threads started by others.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
